;***************************************
@node "About" "Working of WHDAutoLaunch"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "AboutRequirement"

  @{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub} has created to launch automatically a game or demo
  installed by WHDLoad without looking for hard drive location

  You can also choose to open only game's or demo's workbench folder.

  This command will search automatically on harddrive selected game or demo.

  But for that, you must sort WHDLoad's games and demos according to:
                          @{"the sorting protocol" link "TreeProtocol" 0}

  @{b}@{u}WORKING:@{ub}@{uu}
  To @{"launch Game or Demo" link "LaunchGame" 0}, @{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub} use following algorythm:
  --------------------------------------------------------------@{fg fill}
LOCK "DEMOSPATH/DEMOMAKER DEMONAME/"
  IF true
  THEN
    FOUNDPATH="DEMOSPATH/DEMOMAKER DEMONAME/"
    FOUNDSLAVE="DEMONAME.slave"
    CURRENTDIR(FOUNDPATH)
    @{b}Launch "C:Whdload Slave=FOUNDSLAVE Preload"@{ub}
    END
  ELSE
    LOCK "GAMESPATH/"
      IF true
      THEN
        IF (GAMENAME start by letter 0 to 9)
        THEN LOCK "GAMESPATH/0-9/GAMENAME/"
               IF true
               THEN @{u}FOUNDPATH="GAMESPATH/0-9/GAMENAME/"@{uu}: EXIT
               ENDIF
        ENDIF
        IF (GAMENAME start by letter X to Y)
        THEN LOCK "GAMESPATH/X-Y/GAMENAME/"
               IF true
               THEN @{u}FOUNDPATH="GAMESPATH/X-Y/GAMENAME/"@{uu}: EXIT
               ENDIF
        ENDIF
        a=First GAMENAME Letter
        b=Second GAMENAME letter
        DO
          IF b<"A" THEN @{u}FOUNDPATH="GAMESPATH/a/GAMENAME/"@{uu}: EXIT
          ENDIF
          LOCK "GAMESPATH/ab/GAMENAME/"
            IF true THEN @{u}FOUNDPATH="GAMESPATH/ab/GAMENAME/"@{uu}: EXIT
            ENDIF
          b=b-1
        LOOP
      ELSE
        -> Try next Path (5 game path possibles with WHDAutoLaunch V1.1
      ENDIF
  ENDIF

;------------- PATHFOUND
 CURRENTDIR(FOUNDPATH)

;-- Looking for SLAVE= and DATA= parameters using priority list in Prefs file
;NbSuffix is number/2 of priority parameters found in file WHDAutoLaunch.Prefs

n=1
DO
  IF n=NbSuffix+1
  THEN
    FOUNDSLAVE="GAMENAME.slave"
    @{b}Launch "c:whdload Slave=FOUNDSLAVE Preload"@{ub} ; Default Launch
    END
  ENDIF

  LOCK "FOUNDPATH/GAMENAME@{i}Suffix(n)@{ui}.slave)
    IF true
    THEN
      LOCK "FOUNDPATH/@{i}FoundSubDataFolder(n)@{ui}/"
        IF TRUE THEN EXIT
        ENDIF
    ENDIF
  n=n+1
LOOP

DATAFOLDER="FoundSubDataFolder(n)"
FOUNDSLAVE="GAMENAME@{i}FoundSuffix(n)@{ui}.slave"
;
@{b}Launch "c:whdload Slave=FOUNDSLAVE Preload DATA=DATAFOLDER"@{ub}
EXIT

@{fg text}

@endnode


;***************************************
@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Files"
@prev "About"

@{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub} command require following stuffs:

    - @{b}Workbench.library V44@{ub} or better to use @{b}@{"OpenFolder" link "OpenFolder" 0}@{ub} option.


    - @{b}WHDLoad package@{ub} creaded by Bert Jahn (HTTP:/www.whdload.de/)


    - Some demos and games installed on your hardrive with a WHDLoad package and
      located on your hard drive according to @{"the sorting protocol" link "TreeProtocol" 0}


    - A Workbench 3.1 or better installed

@endnode


