;***************************************
@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Config"
@prev "HowInstall"

@{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub} is very easy to install on your HD:

 - Copy file "@{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub}" in @{b}C:@{ub} folder of your Workbench

 - Copy file "@{b}WHDAutoLaunch.prefs@{ub}" in folder @{b}SYS:Prefs/Env-Archive/@{ub}

REMARK:
  File @{b}WHDAutoLaunch.prefs@{ub} is already configurated to find automatically
  standard Slave's name and sub-directory ("DATA=") used for installed
  WHDLoad's games&demos.

@endnode


;***************************************
@node "Config" "Configuration"
@next "TreeProtocol"
@prev "Installation"

@{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub} is simple to configure.

For that you must change @{b}"SYS:Prefs/Env-Archive/WHDAutoLaunch.prefs"@{ub} for
permanent utilization or @{b}"ENV:WHDAutoLaunch.prefs"@{ub} for temporary
utilization.

It's a text file that you can modify with a standard text editor.

@{b}WARNING!@{ub}
maxi size is $400 octets (!1024)

@{u}Structure of this prefs file is following:@{uu}

Line 1: @{b}DEMOSPATH/@{ub} ; warning '/' at the end is required
Line 2: @{b}GAMESPATH1/@{ub} ; warning '/' at the end is required
Line 3: @{b}GAMESPATH2/@{ub} ; warning '/' at the end is required
Line 4: @{b}GAMESPATH3/@{ub} ; warning '/' at the end is required
Line 5: @{b}GAMESPATH4/@{ub} ; warning '/' at the end is required
Line 6: @{b}GAMESPATH5/@{ub} ; warning '/' at the end is required
Line 7: @{b}Option@{ub} ; put here @{b}@{"OpenFolder" link "OpenFolder" 0}@{ub}, @{b}@{"LaunchGame" link "LaunchGame" 0}@{ub}, @{b}@{"Requester" link "Requester" 0}@{ub} or nothing

;now priority list to search good WHDLoad's SLAVE=&DATA= parameters (games only)
;
Line 8: @{b}SlaveSuffix1@{ub} ; try to lock "GAMESPATH/GAMENAMES@{u}SlaveSuffix1@{uu}.slave"
Line 9: @{b}SubDataFolder1@{ub} ;& try to lock "GAMESPATH/@{u}SubDataFolder1@{uu}/"

;If files using previous SLAVE= and DATA= parameters aren't found
; WHDAutoLaunch will try next parameters
Line 10: @{b}SlaveSuffix2@{ub} ; try to lock "GAMESPATH/GAMENAMES@{u}SlaveSuffix2@{uu}.slave"
Line 11: @{b}SubDataFolder2@{ub} ;& try to lock "GAMESPATH/@{u}SubDataFolder2@{uu}/"

;If files using previous SLAVE= and DATA= parameters aren't found
; WHDAutoLaunch will try next parameters
Line 12: @{b}SlaveSuffix3@{ub} ; try to lock "GAMESPATH/GAMENAMES@{u}SlaveSuffix3@{uu}.slave"
Line 13: @{b}SubDataFolder3@{ub} ;& try to lock "GAMESPATH/@{u}SubDataFolder3@{uu}/"
  ...
;If files using previous SLAVE= and DATA= parameters aren't found
; WHDAutoLaunch will try next parameters
Line 24: @{b}SlaveSuffix9@{ub} ; try to lock "GAMESPATH/GAMENAMES@{u}SlaveSuffix9@{uu}.slave"
Line 25: @{b}SubDataFolder9@{ub} ;& try to lock "GAMESPATH/@{u}SubDataFolder9@{uu}/"
  ...

REMARK:
  File @{b}WHDAutoLaunch.prefs@{ub} contents in this package is already configurated
  for standard WHDLoad's @{b}SLAVE=@{ub} and @{b}DATA=@{ub} parameters.

@endnode

;***************************************
@node "TreeProtocol" "Sorting Protocol"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Config"

@{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub} use 2 protocols to sort your installed games and demos on your HD:

      @{u}Sorting protocol for games:@{uu}@{"example " link "TreeProtocolGame" 0})
       |--GAMESPATH/
       |
       @{b}|  |--0-9/     @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--A/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--Ai/      @{ub}; here use second letter that you want (not needed)
       @{b}|  |--Ao/      @{ub}; here use second letter that you want (not needed)
       @{b}|  |--B/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--C/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--Ci/      @{ub}; here use second letter that you want (not needed)
       @{b}|  |--Co/      @{ub}; here use second letter that you want (not needed)
       @{b}|  |--Cr/      @{ub}; here use second letter that you want (not needed)
       @{b}|  |--D/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       |  +--...
       @{b}|  |--V/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--W/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--Wo       @{ub}; here use second letter that you want (not needed)
       @{b}|  |--R/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--X-Y/     @{ub}; This directory is obligatory
       @{b}|  |--Z/       @{ub}; This directory is obligatory

      @{u}Sorting protocol for demos:@{uu}(@{"example" link "TreeProtocolDemo" 0})
       |--DEMOSPATH/@{b}
       |
       |  |--.Various/
       |  |  |--DemoMaker1 DemoName1/
       |  |  |--DemoMaker2 DemoName2/
       |  |  |--DemoMaker3 DemoName3/@{ub}
       |  |  +--...
       |  |@{b}
       |  +--DemoMaker_1/
       |  |  |--DemoName_1_1/
       |  |  |--DemoName_1_2/@{ub}
       |  |  +--...
       |  |@{b}
       |  +--DemoMaker_2/
       |  |  |--DemoName_2_1/@{ub}
       |  +--...

@endnode

