;***************************************
@node "Usage" "USAGE"
@next "GameDemoList"
@prev "TreeProtocol"

It's very easy to use @{b}@{u}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub}@{uu}

First you must @{"configure Prefs file" link "Config" 0} to define PATHs of your demos and games


@{u}FOR GAMES:@{uu}

Use only GAMENAME (name of the main game's folder) as parameter (@{b}without path!@{ub})

USAGE:
        @{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{i} "GameName"@{ui}@{ub}


@{u}FOR DEMOS:@{uu}

Use only final folder path as parameter

USAGE:
        @{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{i} "DemoMaker1/DemoName1"@{ui}@{ub}

      or

        @{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{i} ".various/DemoMaker2 DemoName2"@{ui}@{ub}


But the better way is to use this command in an AmigaGuide file ;)
like @{"WHDGamesDemosList.guide" link "GameDemoList" 0}

@endnode



;***************************************
;***************************************
@node "GameDemoList" "WHDGamesDemosList.guide & WHDGamesDemosListFR.guide"
@next "Tips"
@prev "main"

This package contain a very useful amigaguide in english and french version.

    @{"WHDGamesDemosList.guide" system "SYS:UTILITIES/MULTIVIEW WHDGamesDemosList.guide"} & @{"WHDGamesDemosListFR.guide" system "SYS:UTILITIES/MULTIVIEW WHDGamesDemosListFR.guide"}

It's powerful amiga guide using @{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub} command.

Open it after to have @{"install & configure" link "config" 0} @{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub}

And click on a demo's or game's name to execute "@{b}WHDAutoLaunch@{ub}".

Either option set, @{b}@{"OpenFolder" link "OpenFolder" 0}@{ub}, @{b}@{"LaunchGame" link "LaunchGame" 0}@{ub} or @{b}@{"Requester" link "Requester" 0}@{ub}:

- Selected game/demo's workbench folder will be opened.

- Selected game/demo will launch using @{b}WHDLoad@{ub} created by Bert Jahn

- A requester will appear and ask you to select one of both previous actions

- Or both previous actions if there aren't option set at the third line of file
  "@{"ENV:WHDAutoLaunch.Prefs" link "Config" 0}"
@endnode


